title: For Sale:  Strider Special Mission folding knife
postcontent:
Strider SMF folding knife: Description: Strider Knives is an American owned and operated company. The SMF was specifically developed for Det 1, the first SOCOM unit of the United States Marine Corps. It was also the first tactical knife to be issued within the USMC. The simplified construction gives the knife a lightweight format without sacrificing strength. The history, features, and hard-use nature of the SMF have made it the icon it is today.
The half-and-half construction incorporates a titanium lock-side with a G10 single scale. This hybrid construction lets you have the best of both worlds -- the firm lockup of a framelock with the light weight and grip quality of a G10 handle. The handle incorporates pronounced finger grooves to help you index your grip, and it flares out towards the butt-end to provide a good grip without any backward hand sliding. The titanium pocket clip is mounted for tip-up carry.
The 3.75 inch blade is made from premium S35-VN stainless steel ensuring exceptional edge holding. The Strider SMF pivot screws are oversized for high strength and durability. Handles are screwed together using oversized Torx screws for a very tight fit. Finally, the handle spacer is integral to the G10 scale. It is not a separate piece but rather, machined out of the G10, so the spacer is not a separate piece like with other folders. This extra work ensures that the Strider SMF is a folder that will hold up to hard use. An outstanding example of custom American ingenuity, design, and craftsmanship!

title: For Sale:  glancekooper@yahoo.com
postcontent:
This gun will load on a closed bolt and has a real smooth action.
In addition the extractor has been modified, the feed ramp polished, the rails polished, the extractor ramp modified, the BHO modified, the internal spring for recoil has been changed and the BHO spring modified.
The gun has a Chaos Titan Quad Rail System that hinges up out of the way for easy access to the dust cover.
It also has the Chaos HK Style sights installed.
It has a Custom barrel shroud that has been designed so that a brake such as the Tromix shark brake which is included, can be used with the shroud.
The Bolt Carrier has been completely polished and while the extra work down it's length does not add any performance to the gun it does add some flash.
The charging handle is custom turned and welded to the carrier in the Galil style and then that was polished as well.
The trigger pull is approx 4 lbs.
19" barrel.
An Over Molded Hogue Grip installed.
Paint has been touched up with a solvent resistant Ceramic based paint.

The rear tang has been removed and the rear of the receiver has been reshaped and an internal support block has been installed to support the ACE hardware.
ACE lightweight stock with Foam cheek weld and ACE Push Button folding mechanism with a 1" ACE Butt pad really pads down recoil.
Couple that with a Hogue over molded pistol grip and a Tromix Shark brake which alone reduces felt recoil by 15% and the gun is a dream to shoot.
The gun can be fired with the stock open or folded.
We then drilled a 4th port in the barrel and slightly enlarged the other 3 gas ports to aid in the gun's ability to cycle low brass ammo such as bird shot and the low recoil stuff.
A RAM ambidextrous mag release extension was also added.
An after market recoil spring was also added.

Fire the gun, release a mag, lock open the bolt, all without taking your hand off the pistol grip.
The gun handles flawlessly as all guns modified by our gunsmiths go to the range for testing and 20 or more rounds put through them before shipping.
This is a new gun under warranty-we list it as used because it is not the way it comes from the factory.
The BHO was notched and reshaped for greater reliability and so it doesn't poke into your finger with the trigger in it's new location.
A Krebs Custom safety has been added as well for the fastest use of an AK safety ever. We have even added a detent to help keep the safety from rising too high on the receiver.

title: For Sale/Trade:  LNIB American Derringer in .357 Magnum -- Stainless w/ Rosewood stocks
postcontent:
Here is a rare one for you -- an American Derringer M-1 in .357 Magnum 

It is like new, in the original box. I got it from a guy who said it had never been fired and sat at the back of his safe for years. Then it sat in mine for a while. I cleaned the heavy storage grease off of it, and put it in my pocket a couple times, but I never got around to firing it. . . Basically, it doesn't appear to have even been fired, so it's either new, or like new. 

The AD M-1, is the smallest way to put full-house .357 Magnum in your pocket. Its not the lightest .357 Magnum (the Scandium and Titanium S&W 340PD is 3 oz lighter), but at 15oz, it is pretty light. And, as you can see in the pic next to my old J-frame bodyguard, the M-1 is significantly smaller -- frankly, if it was any smaller or lighter you wouldn't want to fire a powerful round from it, as any 340PD owners can tell you  And, for you Derringer enthusiasts out there, the AD M-1 is about 2/3 the overall size and weight of the Bond Arms derringers with a comparable barrel length, but with a much easier SA hammer and trigger pull. 

The M-1 is nicely made of polished stainless steel and rosewood grips. It features multiple safeties, including a hammer block for safe carry, including pocket carry. Comes with original box, and if you're nice I can toss in some .38 special for practice, and a few rounds of either Hornady .357 Magnum, or Hydra-Shok .38 Special +p+ "Law Enforcement Only" defensive ammo for carry purposes. This is a perfect vest, boot or pocket gun, or a purse gun or garter gun for that special lady.

Asking $450, which is considerably less than similar ones are going for from dealers.  Lowball offers will be ignored. 

Looking to do a FTF transaction in the Portland Metro area only. OR DL required, CHL preferred.

The Glockworx Fulcrum Trigger is the only Glock trigger on the planet that is engineered with innovative features conveniently housed within the trigger pad, for the ultimate performance experience, in a sleek, seamless design.

This unique, proprietary, fully adjustable (drop-in) trigger is CNC machined from billet 6061 T6 aluminum and hard anodized to withstand the affects of environmental stress and chemical exposure. The Fulcrum Trigger offers both pre-travel take-up and over-travel engagement adjustments, thus providing the user with optimal control and customizability.

Tuning action is achieved by two opposing, conveniently located 2/56" adjustment screws. This quality allows the user to precisely tune the feel of the trigger to his or her preferred specifications, including desired pull weight and fore and aft travel distance.

The Fulcrum Trigger utilizes a distinctive, spring loaded, anatomical engagement safety, which maintains full responsiveness and reliability without ever sacrificing safety. The Fulcrum Trigger's precision-machined trigger bar boasts mirror polishing on all engagement and contact surfaces. This element greatly increases the sensitivity and overall performance of the trigger.

The Fulcrum Trigger is compatible with all Glock 9mm from Generations 1 through 4, and is easily installed by the consumer. The dynamic features of the Fulcrum Trigger allow the shooter to transform their factory Glock trigger into a highly accurate, dynamic and reliable trigger system.

Set screws in front and back of the trigger to adjust over travel and pre travel.

title: For Sale:  Military unit match pistol .45 ACP 1911
postcontent:
This is a Unit match pistol from the US Military. Likely from the 60s or 70s. This pistol was built for accuracy.
 Built with all military parts including National match slide, BBL, bushing,front sight, and Bo Mar rear sight. Slide to frame fit is tight. These guns were often built on Commercial Colt or Essex frames so that the pistol belonged to the match shooter, rather than the US Government. If it was built on a WWII frame, it belonged to Uncle Sam, and had to be left behind when the soldier was transfered to another duty station. Also the commercial frames held a Match grade " tune up " better because the steel was a lot better in the 60s or 70s than in the 40s. This one is built on an Exxex frame.The pistol is in excellent condition. No Calif sales. Face to face in Oklahoma with OK drivers license. FFL required outside OK. $35 covers transfer and shipping.
